messageBody:
Message
Hi Oliver,
 
I created that Zip using WinZip on a Windows machine. Because of size limitations within Yahoo I had to find a way to make is smaller.
 
I'll split the orignal file into a couple sections and then create seperate stand alone Zip files that do not need to be linked.
 
I should have them up on the site within the day.
 
 
Chuck
-----Original Message-----
From: oliver langan [mailto:yahoo@...]
Sent: Monday, August 02, 2004 1:24 AM
To: Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [Read_Alphabet] Re: among and above have

> This is from the dictionary that is located in the "Files
> <http://groups.yahoo.com/group/Read_Alphabet/files/>  > Resources" section
> of the web site. That dictionary was build from a phonic database.

I have tried to download that dictionary several times, and I just can't get the two halves to
combine into a 'real' file.  Could you please upload it again as a single file, or perhaps
explain to me how you originally unzipped it?  I am using a Mac (and thus have access to
unix command-line tools also).  I'd love to play with it!

oliver
